  <num>28:1-205</num>
  <heading>Reasonable time; seasonableness.</heading>
  <level>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Whether a time for taking an action required by this subtitle is reasonable depends on the nature, purpose, and circumstances of the action.</text>
  </level>
  <level>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>An action is taken seasonably if it is taken at or within the time agreed or, if no time is agreed, at or within a reasonable time.</text>
  </level>
